# Poker Trainer Project

## Tech Stack

- React 18+ with TypeScript
- Vite for bundling/dev server
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Zustand for state management (two stores: gameStore, rangeStore)
- localStorage for persistence of user settings and custom hand ranges
- No backend — entirely client-side

## Architecture

```
App
+-- Header (NextHandButton, DealButton, BlindsAnteEditor, SettingsDropdown)
+-- MainLayout (flex row: TableArea + RangeSidebar)
|   +-- TableArea
|   |   +-- PokerTable (oval green felt, CSS positioned)
|   |   |   +-- Seat[] (absolutely positioned around ellipse)
|   |   |   +-- CommunityCards (center)
|   |   |   +-- PotDisplay (center)
|   |   +-- ActionPanel (fold/call/raise + BetSizer)
|   +-- RangeSidebar (scrollable, one mini range chart per active player)
+-- CardPickerModal (4x13 grid overlay)
+-- RangeEditorModal (full-screen, all positions)
+-- ContextMenu (right-click: "Sit Here", "Set Dealer")
```

## State Management

- `src/store/gameStore.ts` — Game state: players, street, pot, community cards, dealer, active player, settings (seat count, blinds, antes)
- `src/store/rangeStore.ts` — Range profiles: per-position ranges keyed by action scenario, persisted to localStorage
- `src/store/actionLogic.ts` — Pure functions for action sequencing, pot math, street transitions

## Key Types (defined in `src/types/index.ts`)

- `Position`: 'UTG' | 'UTG+1' | 'UTG+2' | 'LJ' | 'HJ' | 'CO' | 'BTN' | 'SB' | 'BB'
- `Rank`: 'A' | 'K' | 'Q' | 'J' | 'T' | '9' | '8' | '7' | '6' | '5' | '4' | '3' | '2'
- `Suit`: 'spades' | 'hearts' | 'diamonds' | 'clubs'
- `Card`: { rank: Rank; suit: Suit }
- `HandRange`: boolean[][] (13x13 grid)
- `ActionScenario`: 'open' | 'vsRaiseCall' | 'vsRaise3Bet' | 'vs3BetCall' | 'vs3Bet4Bet'

## File Conventions

- Components in `src/components/` — one component per file, PascalCase filenames
- Utility functions in `src/utils/` — pure functions, camelCase filenames
- Data files in `src/data/` — static default data (ranges, etc.)
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes over custom CSS
- Use Zustand `useStore` hooks for state access in components

